name: The pain that never ends
description: I was used to listening to and photographing stories that pained me. However, in my line of work, I rarely find myself as the direct topic of the subject. I've lived in a lot of different nations. Too many studios were opened and shuttered by me. She arrived to my studio one day with the man she had married. As if they didn't know who I was, she stated they wanted to go into the shop and have their picture taken. We didn't want our relationship to end, but she wanted me to see and capture the anguish she was going through so I would never forget her. This photo proves beyond a shadow of a doubt that we have nothing left to share but our pain.
